;
; Object Script
;
;
;
;
;

; a=the item
; h=his/her
; i=him/her
; s=he/she

INUMBER 925
NAME 536
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
ARTICLE your
HIDDEN

IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
IFVAR ITEMVAL3 < 7
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You listen to the object intently.
  ECHO PLAYER

  IFVAR FLAG3 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "These are the rules governing the use of the object. Failure to comply with the following rules may result in a gory death witnessed by all the GM's."
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "If you've heard this before, just cycle through the rules, and you'll never see them again. If you have not had an object before, pay attention!"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "Rule 1: Don't flaunt the object! Do not do this:"
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You bug your eyes out.
    ECHO PLAYER You exclaim, "Hey, everyone, I have an object!"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "Rule 5: Experiment with the commands all you like, but do
    ECHO PLAYER so in private. When determining its functions, make sure you are in an inn
    ECHO PLAYER room, or another non-public area."
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 3
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "Rule 3: While the object exists as an item in the game,
    ECHO PLAYER it does not "exist" in-character. Do not speak about it or refer to it in-
    ECHO PLAYER character."
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "Rule 4: The object is non-transferable between players and
    ECHO PLAYER characters. Do not give your object to anyone, do not drop it anywhere, and
    ECHO PLAYER do not put it into a container!"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 5
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "Rule 2: You may tell people how to obtain an object, but they must inquire first:"
    ECHO PLAYER
    ECHO PLAYER Mathlesia whispers to you, "[Hey, how do you bug your eyes out?]"
    ECHO PLAYER You whisper to Malthesia, "[See a GM about getting an Object.]"
    ECHO PLAYER Malthesia whispers to you, "[Thank you, I am eternally in your debt.]"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 = 6
    ECHO PLAYER The object says, "That's about it. Just don't abuse the object, and you're all set. If you have any questions, ask Iduiin. And remember, a good role-player always hits other people repeatedly."
    EQUAL ITEMVAL3 7
    GMMSG ** %N's object has been outfitted.
  ENDIF

  ADD FLAG3 1
ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB BREAK -1
  CLEARVERB
ELSE
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 2
  ENDIF

  IFVAR RAC ! 11
    ; Increment each time user uses it since December 26, 1993.
    ADD ITEMVAL2 1
  ENDIF
ENDIF

